That was the start

242
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:46,479
of the Raijin Junior High
Biology Club.

243
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:47,981
Then, during our summer break‐‐

244
00:10:53,736 --> 00:10:55,613
SHINRA: I'm expecting
great things from you,

245
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:56,865
Vice President.

246
00:10:56,865 --> 00:10:58,324
‐ So what you're saying is,

247
00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:00,535
you're not gonna do a thing,
Mr. President?

248
00:11:00,535 --> 00:11:03,621
‐ No, not exactly.
I'll be cheering you on.

249
00:11:03,621 --> 00:11:05,999
We're officially
a two‐member club.

250
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:08,793
That means you can come up
with your own activities.

251
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:11,379
What do you say?
‐ 'Kay, then.

252
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:14,632
If you die here, I propose
to observe how your corpse rots,

253
00:11:14,632 --> 00:11:16,593
then exhibit it
at the cultural festival.

254
00:11:16,593 --> 00:11:19,971
Right. American universities
have research facilities

255
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:21,431
where they do
that kind of stuff.

256
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:24,142
They call them body farms.
Pretty creepy, huh?

257
00:11:24,142 --> 00:11:26,561
‐ How do you know that?
‐ My dad does research

258
00:11:26,561 --> 00:11:28,605
for a pharmaceutical company
there.

259
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:31,482
He tells me all kinds
of cool trivia like that.

260
00:11:31,482 --> 00:11:33,109
I just thought of something.

261
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:35,945
What are you gonna do
if my body doesn't decompose?

262
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:37,280
‐ Huh?

263
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,157
‐ Let's suppose you have
a female corpse‐‐

264
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:42,076
a gorgeous female corpse
with her heart intact,

265
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:44,495
and say her corpse
doesn't rot.

266
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:46,581
People would just see
a beautiful corpse,

267
00:11:46,581 --> 00:11:50,335
but what if you saw her
as the love of your life?

268
00:11:50,335 --> 00:11:53,713
And what if you want to find out
how she feels about you?

269
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:55,423
I mean, she's a corpse.

270
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:58,301
‐ Well, if you're crazy enough,
I guess you can

271
00:11:58,301 --> 00:12:00,678
fake talking to her
with ventriloquism.

272
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:02,847
‐ Let's say
this beautiful woman's corpse

273
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:05,683
that doesn't rot
can also walk around?

274
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,310
In other words,
it went from being

275
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:11,022
a non‐decomposing corpse
to a non‐decomposing zombie.

276
00:12:11,022 --> 00:12:12,941
If you could talk to her,
do you think

277
00:12:12,941 --> 00:12:15,026
it would be possible
to fall in love with her?

278
00:12:15,026 --> 00:12:16,527
‐ Are you serious?

279
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:18,571
‐ Suppose all the zombie's
internals are fine,

280
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:21,366
just the heart stopped,
and suppose you could talk

281
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:23,868
and joke around with her?
What would that be like?

282
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:26,204
‐ I guess it'd be the same
as talking to a person

283
00:12:26,204 --> 00:12:28,790
without a heartbeat
and a funny way of walking.

284
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:30,583
‐ Then it wouldn't be weird
to fall in love

285
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,377
with that zombie, would it?

286
00:12:32,377 --> 00:12:34,045
I mean, if it's normal
to love a human

287
00:12:34,045 --> 00:12:37,674
but abnormal to love a zombie,
what do you do then?

288
00:12:37,674 --> 00:12:41,261
Where do you draw the line?

289
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:43,221
‐ Well, I don't think
it really matters

290
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:45,723
who you fall in love with.
It's cool as long as

291
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:48,309
you don't hurt anyone, right?
‐ Uh‐uhh.

292
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:51,479
I'd gladly hurt someone,
'cause I love her.

293
00:12:53,231 --> 00:12:56,067
‐ Wow. Seriously?
‐ You know it!

294
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:58,027
Even back then I loved you
as much as‐‐

295
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,946
[bones cracking]
[groans] Ow.

296
00:12:59,946 --> 00:13:01,656
Without you...
‐ Take it easy,

297
00:13:01,656 --> 00:13:03,324
don't get excited.
‐ Life is just a big, black...

298
00:13:03,324 --> 00:13:04,575
‐ Okay, I get it, I get it.
Easy, it's okay.

299
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:07,370
‐ Icky hole of despair.

300
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:11,249
Guess I overdid it.
Sorry for spazzing out.

301
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:13,501
‐ It's fine,
please just stay in bed.

302
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:16,963
‐ The next month was
when it happened.

303
00:13:16,963 --> 00:13:18,089
[baseball announcements]
SHINRA: Oh, come on,

304
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,507
we talked about this.

305
00:13:19,507 --> 00:13:21,926
You were gonna stop taking bets
on baseball games.

306
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:23,720
‐ Stop nagging me.

307
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,555
It's none of your business
anyway.

308
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:27,473
‐ Actually, it is my business,

309
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:29,934
'cause I already told my family
you're my friend.

310
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:31,644
‐ So what?
‐ So if you're doing

311
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,771
something illegal at school
and I don't say

312
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:36,649
something about it,
that's not right.

313
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:39,027
‐ Shinra, are you an idiot?

314
00:13:39,027 --> 00:13:41,446
'Cause right now it sounds like
you can't make a decision

315
00:13:41,446 --> 00:13:43,781
without worrying
about what other people think.

316
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:44,949
You're like a puppet.

317
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:46,951
‐ But if that person is
someone I love,

318
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:50,121
I wouldn't mind being
their puppet at all.

319
00:13:50,121 --> 00:13:52,623
‐ You're hopeless,
you know that?

320
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:55,960
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

321
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:58,463
‐ [groans]
MAN: Kishitani, what happened?

322
00:13:58,463 --> 00:14:00,631
‐ I guess I got stabbed.

323
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:03,634
Would you call an ambulance,
please?

324
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:04,802
[siren wailing]

325
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:06,471
NAKURA:
[voiceover] A few hours later,

326
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:08,473
Izaya surrendered to the police
and was taken into custody.

327
00:14:08,473 --> 00:14:10,725
We didn't press charges though,
and it was over

328
00:14:10,725 --> 00:14:13,144
before too many people
found out about it.

329
00:14:13,144 --> 00:14:14,604
<i>♪ ♪</i>

330
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:16,481
‐ Wait, it was Izaya?

331
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:19,609
Are you telling me
Izaya stabbed you?

332
00:14:19,609 --> 00:14:22,153
All right, now I'm mad‐‐
really mad!

333
00:14:22,153 --> 00:14:23,613
‐ No, calm down, Celty.
‐ I'll make that rotten,

334
00:14:23,613 --> 00:14:24,989
no‐good‐‐
‐ It's not like that?

335
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:27,700
‐ Huh?
‐ It‐‐that's not what happened.

336
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:30,411
‐ Well, then what did happen?

337
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:31,454
‐ [groans]

338
00:14:31,454 --> 00:14:33,164
<i>♪ ♪</i>

339
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:35,833
[breathes deeply]

340
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,210
‐ Now you're sleeping?

341
00:14:41,172 --> 00:14:42,507
[phone ringing]

342
00:14:42,507 --> 00:14:46,511
‐ Hi, Nakura. Nice work.
You're a good actor.

343
00:14:46,511 --> 00:14:49,972
‐ Huh?
Wait, were you listening in?

344
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:52,475
IZAYA: Yep,
I heard every single lie.

345
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:53,810
NAKURA: What did you
get me into?

346
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:55,728
That lady's
no insurance agent.

347
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,939
Is she Yakuza?
Look, I don't want

348
00:14:57,939 --> 00:14:59,607
anything to do with that stuff,
ever.

349
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:04,278
‐ Oh, my. Someone's honed
their observation skills.

350
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:06,781
You're right, she's not
an insurance agent,

351
00:15:06,781 --> 00:15:08,282
nor does she work for one.

352
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:11,911
Her name really is
Kasane Kujiragi though.

353
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,704
And don't worry
about the Yakuza.

354
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:15,206
This is different.

355
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:16,999
NAKURA: A‐are you sure
about that?

356
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:19,210
IZAYA: Super sure,
although you almost had

357
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:23,381
the Awakusu coming after you
for two different reasons.

358
00:15:23,381 --> 00:15:25,007
‐ What?
IZAYA: Remember that thing

359
00:15:25,007 --> 00:15:28,553
we started our senior year
of high school, Amphisbaena?

360
00:15:28,553 --> 00:15:32,056
‐ Oh, that thing?
Yeah, I do.

361
00:15:32,056 --> 00:15:33,349
It was just a bigger version

362
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:35,309
of our betting pool
for baseball.

363
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:36,602
IZAYA: That's the one.

364
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,646
I believe you
called yourself Tokage.

365
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:41,065
‐ Right, but it was only around
for a little while.

366
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:43,025
IZAYA: Well, do you remember
a girl back then

367
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:45,528
whose nickname was Mimizu?

368
00:15:45,528 --> 00:15:47,363
‐ No. I don't.

369
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:48,489
IZAYA: I don't either.

370
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:50,575
In fact,
I've never heard of her.

371
00:15:50,575 --> 00:15:52,451
Anyway,
she took over Amphisbaena

372
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:55,913
and she's been doing business
with it on the Awakusu's turf.

373
00:15:55,913 --> 00:15:57,123
‐ Huh?

374
00:15:57,123 --> 00:15:58,624
IZAYA:
Oh, you should've heard her.

375
00:15:58,624 --> 00:15:59,917
She was going on and on,

376
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:01,836
"the boss" this
and "the boss" that.

377
00:16:01,836 --> 00:16:03,129
She worshipped you.

378
00:16:03,129 --> 00:16:04,881
I guess she thought
she was your lover,

379
00:16:04,881 --> 00:16:06,841
and she made everyone
think that too,

380
00:16:06,841 --> 00:16:09,135
even though you're not
the boss anymore.

381
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:10,761
NAKURA: All right,
what's the deal?

382
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:12,972
Where's this going?
‐ Don't worry.

383
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:15,391
Everything's been
taken care of.

384
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:17,643
Oh, do you want to know
what's even funnier?

385
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:19,437
She was locking horns
with Shijima.

386
00:16:19,437 --> 00:16:20,688
Can you beat that?

387
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:21,939
NAKURA: What?
‐ [laughs]

388
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:22,940
NAKURA: You mean
the guy who started

389
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,233
that underground drug club?

390
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:26,485
‐ That's right,
rich boy Shijima.

391
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:28,654
I never met him back then,
but you did,

392
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:31,240
and if memory serves,
you co‐founded the club with him

393
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,867
and called yourself Kumoi.

394
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:35,912
Well, now he's moved up
to making harder drugs,

395
00:16:35,912 --> 00:16:37,496
'cause that's what
Mr. Kumoi wants.

396
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:39,290
NAKURA: Wait, hold on!
IZAYA: It's funny.

397
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:41,125
‐ You're kidding!
IZAYA: Nope,

398
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:43,377
Shijima calls himself
"the second in command,"

399
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:45,463
and get this,
he keeps his people in line

400
00:16:45,463 --> 00:16:49,342
by hurting himself and saying
Kumoi did it to punish him.

401
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:51,802
This Kumoi sure sounds
like a bastard, huh?

402
00:16:51,802 --> 00:16:54,972
‐ [panting] This is crazy.
I can't get involved with this!

403
00:16:54,972 --> 00:16:57,266
What am I gonna do?
IZAYA: Calm down.

404
00:16:57,266 --> 00:16:59,477
You don't have to worry
about Shijima.

405
00:16:59,477 --> 00:17:01,103
‐ For real?
IZAYA: Sure.

406
00:17:01,103 --> 00:17:03,856
You don't have anything to worry
about from anyone,

407
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:06,484
and if things do go south,
you can always have Shinra

408
00:17:06,484 --> 00:17:08,027
change your face again.

409
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:11,322
NAKURA: [sobbing] But I‐‐
I gotta‐‐what am I gonna do?

410
00:17:11,322 --> 00:17:14,450
‐ Nothing. Hey, if you
don't like where you're at now,

411
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:16,160
complain to your past self
about it.

412
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:19,664
Okay, then, talk to you later.
Bye.

413
00:17:19,664 --> 00:17:21,374
NAKURA: [whimpering]

414
00:17:21,374 --> 00:17:25,336
Why?
Why's this happening to me?

415
00:17:25,336 --> 00:17:29,048
Shit. Shit. Shit! Shit!

416
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:33,344
‐ I wouldn't mind being
their puppet at all.

417
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:35,680
‐ You're hopeless,
you know that?

418
00:17:36,931 --> 00:17:38,057
NAKURA: Orihara.

419
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:40,142
‐ Hey. What's up, Nakura?

420
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:42,520
Sorry, betting's closed
for today.

421
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:47,233
‐ I know. Listen, man,
that bet I made yesterday, I‐‐

422
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,443
I want to cancel it,
I need the cash back.

423
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:51,153
I need it now,
before my dad finds out

424
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:53,698
I took it from his wallet.
He'll kick my ass!

425
00:17:53,698 --> 00:17:55,533
‐ That's your problem,
not mine.

426
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:58,452
I never forced you to place
any bets, that was all you.

427
00:17:58,452 --> 00:17:59,704
NAKURA: [whimpering]

428
00:17:59,704 --> 00:18:02,206
‐ Oh, Nakura.
Drop the knife, man.

429
00:18:02,206 --> 00:18:04,542
‐ Shut up.
I want my money back!

430
00:18:04,542 --> 00:18:06,168
Come on! Give it to me!
IZAYA: Not gonna happen.

431
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:09,714
Giving you your cash back
won't do me any favors.

432
00:18:09,714 --> 00:18:11,882
I know you.
When someone wins,

433
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:13,884
you're there,
asking for a handout.

434
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,303
We've gotten complaints.

435
00:18:15,303 --> 00:18:17,680
‐ No. It's a lie.
Give me back my money!

436
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:19,724
‐ You're such a moron.

437
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:21,225
‐ No! [grunts]

438
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:23,477
[wincing]
‐ [whimpers]

439
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:26,939
SHINRA: [wincing]
NAKURA: No. No, no.

440
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:31,110
No. I‐I was just trying
to scare Orihara. I was‐‐

441
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:32,069
‐ [wincing]

442
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:34,363
‐ I didn't‐‐I didn't!

443
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:37,074
No! No!

444
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:39,285
‐ Hang on.
I'll call an ambulance.

445
00:18:39,285 --> 00:18:42,496
‐ No, wait. Duct tape.

446
00:18:42,496 --> 00:18:46,417
I gotta stop‐‐stop
the bleeding first.

447
00:18:46,417 --> 00:18:47,877
[chuckles]

448
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:50,755
I guess I'm not much of a hero,
huh?

449
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:53,466
I was hoping to impress someone
with my bravery.

450
00:18:53,466 --> 00:18:55,092
[groans]
‐ Don't talk.

451
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:57,011
‐ No, I'm fine.

452
00:18:57,011 --> 00:18:59,221
He didn't hit
any internal organs.

453
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:03,768
[groaning]
‐ Hey, Shinra, I have an idea.

454
00:19:03,768 --> 00:19:06,687
Do you mind if we play this
as if I stabbed you?

455
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,939
‐ Why?
‐ Yes or no.

456
00:19:08,939 --> 00:19:10,983
And if you say yes,

457
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:14,111
I'll spend my life
making Nakura regret it.

458
00:19:14,111 --> 00:19:16,364
‐ So, what did you tell him?

459
00:19:16,364 --> 00:19:19,116
‐ Um, "Go ahead," I guess.

460
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:21,494
‐ I knew you could be ruthless
from time to time,

461
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:23,537
but that was ruthless.

462
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:25,164
‐ [chuckles]

463
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,625
I play the straight arrow
'cause I know it turns you on.

464
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:31,128
‐ Who knew Izaya would
deal justice like that?

465
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,463
‐ He and I are different,

466
00:19:32,463 --> 00:19:33,881
but we're both
full of surprises.

467
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:35,758
[chuckles]
Maybe he did it

468
00:19:35,758 --> 00:19:37,843
because he thought
it would be fun.

469
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:40,680
‐ On this latest job, he had me
get some gambling chips,

470
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,306
let someone steal
a laptop off me...

471
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:44,558
[cell doors slamming shut]
And keep his little sister safe.

472
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:47,520
[all groaning]

473
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:50,439
‐ Just in time.
Thank you.

474
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:52,983
‐ If you want to thank someone,
thank your brother.

475
00:19:52,983 --> 00:19:54,443
‐ No way, really?

476
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:55,528
[phone ringing]

477
00:19:55,528 --> 00:19:57,029
‐ Hey, you okay?

478
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:58,447
I just got jumped
by these goons,

479
00:19:58,447 --> 00:19:59,949
but Master Eijirou came
in the nick of time

480
00:19:59,949 --> 00:20:01,283
and beat 'em all to mush.

481
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,827
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]
So what about you?

482
00:20:02,827 --> 00:20:04,704
Did you get attacked too?

483
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:08,499
CELTY: My opinion about you
changed today.

484
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:09,834
You worry about your family,

485
00:20:09,834 --> 00:20:11,836
just like any normal person
would.

486
00:20:11,836 --> 00:20:13,671
‐ I don't know about that.

487
00:20:13,671 --> 00:20:16,132
The harder you try to see
the good in people,

488
00:20:16,132 --> 00:20:18,217
the easier it is
to fake you out.

489
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:22,722
‐ Thanks.
Now what about the name?

490
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:26,392
‐ Right. Although it might be
a bit hard to believe‐‐

491
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:28,602
‐ Just tell me.
‐ [chuckles]

492
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:30,855
Jinnai Yodogiri.

493
00:20:30,855 --> 00:20:34,608
He's the mastermind who had
that stalker attack Shinra.

494
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:38,404
Or maybe he's playing
the mastermind, who knows?

495
00:20:38,404 --> 00:20:41,115
‐ And where is he now?
‐ I'm tracking him.

496
00:20:41,115 --> 00:20:43,951
And if I do find him,
it's gonna cost you extra.

497
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:45,286
‐ Hey.
‐ Hmm?

498
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,415
‐ No, never mind.

499
00:20:49,415 --> 00:20:50,875
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

500
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:52,752
IZAYA: [voiceover]
You're wrong, transporter.

501
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:54,712
I asked you to protect
my sisters

502
00:20:54,712 --> 00:20:56,672
because I didn't want them
to come to the bar

503
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:58,507
where Haruna Niekawa was.

504
00:20:58,507 --> 00:21:01,010
That's all there is to that.
[phone ringing]

505
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:03,804
Oh, well, the transporter
didn't ask for it.

506
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,848
I'm pretty sure she knew
it was here though.

507
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:08,768
‐ Just when I thought
you couldn't get any lower.

508
00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:10,644
As much as I hate
The Headless Rider,

509
00:21:10,644 --> 00:21:12,188
what you're doing is wrong.

510
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:14,982
I think I'm starting
to feel sorry for her.

511
00:21:14,982 --> 00:21:18,402
I mean, technically speaking,
her head seduced Seiji,

512
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:21,322
not the rest of her.
‐ Yes, well,

513
00:21:21,322 --> 00:21:24,116
I knew she wouldn't demand
I hand it over,

514
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:27,745
which is good, because I wanted
to see if there'd be any...

515
00:21:27,745 --> 00:21:29,288
change to it.

516
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,373
Nope, it looks the same.

517
00:21:32,416 --> 00:21:35,503
‐ I'm sure I felt it back there.

518
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:39,089
[footsteps]

519
00:21:39,089 --> 00:21:41,050
I knew it.

520
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:43,469
He's got my head.

521
00:21:43,469 --> 00:21:45,262
Why though?

522
00:21:45,262 --> 00:21:50,017
You'll never change, Izaya.
I can't trust you.

523
00:21:50,017 --> 00:21:52,311
MAIRU: Look, there he is!
Wait up, Izaya!

524
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:54,396
‐ Hmm?
‐ Izaya!

525
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:55,981
‐ Hey! [laughs]
‐ Hey, guys,

526
00:21:55,981 --> 00:21:57,149
thanks for calling out

527
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:59,151
before trying to kick me
in the head.

528
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:01,320
‐ That's 'cause I don't think
you're a butt hole anymore.

529
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,905
I hear that you asked
The Headless Rider

530
00:22:02,905 --> 00:22:05,074
to protect Kururi.
Is that for real, or what?

531
00:22:05,074 --> 00:22:07,201
‐ Did you really?
‐ Oh, I had something

532
00:22:07,201 --> 00:22:09,537
I didn't want The Headless Rider
knowing about.

533
00:22:09,537 --> 00:22:12,498
If you want to know the truth,
I used you as a decoy.

534
00:22:12,498 --> 00:22:15,876
‐ Whatever, that's cool.
Thanks, Izaya.

535
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:17,711
‐ Thanks a lot.

536
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:19,255
‐ [chuckles]

537
00:22:19,255 --> 00:22:22,049
After all these years,
I still can't figure you out.

538
00:22:22,049 --> 00:22:24,552
MAIRU: Well, maybe you would
if you weren't so darn crooked.

539
00:22:24,552 --> 00:22:26,929
KURURI: And stubborn.

540
00:22:26,929 --> 00:22:30,057
<i>["Never Say Never"</i>
<i>by Three Lights Down Kings]</i>

541
00:22:30,057 --> 00:22:33,143
<i>[man singing in Japanese]</i>

542
00:22:33,143 --> 00:22:40,150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

